# Frontend Product Requirements Document (PRD)
**Project:** Enterprise AI Onboarding & Compliance Accelerator (Agentic LMS)  
**Stack:** React.js (via Vite) + CSS Modules  
**Document Version:** v2.0 (Finalized — Cross-Referenced with Backend)  
**Last Updated:** 2026-05-09

---

## 1. Frontend System Specification (UI Spec)

### 1.1. Core Requirements

| ID | Requirement | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| FR-01 | **SPA (Single Page Application):** No page reloads. All view transitions managed via React state. | Prevents loss of streaming connection and in-memory chat history. |
| FR-02 | **Real-time SSE Streaming:** Chat component must parse `text/event-stream` from `POST` endpoint using `fetch()` + `ReadableStream` (not `EventSource`, which only supports `GET`). | Backend uses `POST` for chat (because it sends a JSON body). `EventSource` API cannot do `POST`. |
| FR-03 | **Asynchronous UI Blocking:** Disable chat input when `agentState` is `typing`, `evaluating`, or `requires_approval`. | Prevents user from sending overlapping messages while the graph is mid-execution. Backend does not queue multiple invocations per session. |
| FR-04 | **Graceful Error Display:** Catch SSE `error` events and display a non-technical, user-friendly toast/banner. | Backend emits `event: error` with `{"detail": "..."}` on failures. |
| FR-05 | **Auto-Scroll:** Chat window must auto-scroll to the latest message during streaming. User scroll-up should pause auto-scroll (chat app UX pattern). | Standard chat UX best practice. |
| FR-06 | **Responsive Layout:** Must be functional on screens ≥ 1024px. Mobile is out-of-scope for MVP. | Enterprise dashboards are primarily used on desktops. |

### 1.2. State Management (React `useState` / Context)

The application will maintain a centralized state, lifting state to `<App />` or using React Context:

```typescript
interface AppState {
  // === Session ===
  session: {
    session_id: string;
    employee_name: string;
    employee_role: string;
  } | null;

  // === Chat ===
  messages: Array<{
    role: 'user' | 'assistant' | 'system';
    content: string;
    agent?: string;              // e.g., "explainer_node", "assessor_node"
    timestamp: Date;
  }>;

  // === Agent Lifecycle ===
  agentState: 'idle' | 'typing' | 'evaluating' | 'requires_approval';
  activeAgent: string | null;    // Currently executing node name

  // === Curriculum Progress ===
  syllabus: string[];            // Full ordered topic list from Planner
  completedTopics: string[];     // Topics passed
  currentTopic: string;          // Active topic

  // === Assessment ===
  quizScore: number;             // 0–100
  isCertified: boolean;

  // === Supervisor HITL ===
  requiresApproval: boolean;     // True when graph is interrupted
  pendingNodes: string[];        // e.g., ["certifier_node"]
}
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The `syllabus` array is populated at session creation (returned by `POST /sessions`). The `completedTopics`, `quizScore`, and `currentTopic` are updated via the `state_update` SSE event during chat streaming.

### 1.3. Component Architecture

```text
<App />
├── <SetupScreen />              — Session creation form
└── <DashboardLayout />          — Main 2-column grid
    ├── <Sidebar />              — Left panel
    │   ├── <ProfileCard />      — Name, Role, Avatar
    │   ├── <SyllabusTracker />  — Topic checklist with progress
    │   └── <ScorePanel />       — Live quiz score + certification status
    ├── <ChatWindow />           — Right/main panel
    │   ├── <MessageList />      — Scrollable message container
    │   │   └── <MessageBubble /> — Individual message (user vs assistant styling)
    │   ├── <TypingIndicator />  — "Agent is thinking..." animation
    │   └── <ChatInput />        — Textarea + Send button (disabled during agent work)
    └── <SupervisorModal />      — Glassmorphism overlay (conditionally rendered)
```

> [!NOTE]
> `<SupervisorModal />` is rendered conditionally when `requiresApproval === true`. In a production multi-user system, the Supervisor would have a separate portal. For this portfolio MVP, both roles (Trainee + Supervisor) share the same UI, with the modal simulating the supervisor's action.

