## 2. User Flow Diagram

### 2.1. Primary Flow (Happy Path)

```mermaid
graph TD
    Start([User Opens App]) --> SetupView[Setup Screen]
    SetupView -->|Fill Name + Role| CallCreate["POST /api/v1/sessions"]
    CallCreate --> ReceiveSession["Receive: session_id, welcome_message, syllabus[]"]
    ReceiveSession --> Dashboard[Dashboard View]
    
    Dashboard --> UserTypes[User Types Message]
    UserTypes --> CallChat["POST /api/v1/sessions/{id}/chat"]
    
    CallChat --> SSEStream{SSE Event Stream}
    
    SSEStream -->|"event: agent_start"| ShowTyping["Show 'Agent is thinking...'"]
    SSEStream -->|"event: token"| AppendToken["Append token to chat bubble"]
    SSEStream -->|"event: agent_end"| HideTyping["Hide typing indicator"]
    SSEStream -->|"event: state_update"| UpdateSidebar["Update Score, Topics, Current Topic"]
    SSEStream -->|"event: done"| ReEnable["Re-enable chat input"]
    SSEStream -->|"event: requires_approval"| ShowModal["Show Supervisor Modal"]
    SSEStream -->|"event: error"| ShowError["Show error toast"]
    
    ShowModal --> SupervisorActs{Supervisor Decision}
    SupervisorActs -->|Approve| CallApprove["POST /api/v1/sessions/{id}/approve"]
    SupervisorActs -->|Reject| CallReject["POST /api/v1/sessions/{id}/reject"]
    
    CallApprove --> CertResult["Show certification message"]
    CallReject --> Dashboard
```

### 2.2. Edge Cases & Guards

```mermaid
graph TD
    UserSends[User Sends Message] --> CheckCertified{isCertified?}
    CheckCertified -->|Yes| BlockMsg["Backend returns: 'Already certified'"]
    CheckCertified -->|No| CheckApproval{requiresApproval?}
    CheckApproval -->|Yes| BlockMsg2["Backend returns: 'Awaiting supervisor'"]
    CheckApproval -->|No| Proceed[Proceed to SSE Stream]
```

> [!TIP]
> Both guards are implemented server-side in `chat.py` (lines 193-212), returning a non-streaming `ChatResponse` JSON. The frontend should detect non-SSE responses (Content-Type = `application/json` vs `text/event-stream`) and handle them as system messages.

