## 4. API Integration Contract

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This contract has been **verified line-by-line** against the actual backend source code:
> - [requests.py](file:///d:/ProjectAI/LangGraph%20-%20Enterprise%20AI%20Onboarding%20&%20Compliance%20Accelerator%20(Agentic%20LMS)/src/schemas/requests.py)
> - [responses.py](file:///d:/ProjectAI/LangGraph%20-%20Enterprise%20AI%20Onboarding%20&%20Compliance%20Accelerator%20(Agentic%20LMS)/src/schemas/responses.py)
> - [sessions.py](file:///d:/ProjectAI/LangGraph%20-%20Enterprise%20AI%20Onboarding%20&%20Compliance%20Accelerator%20(Agentic%20LMS)/src/api/sessions.py)
> - [chat.py](file:///d:/ProjectAI/LangGraph%20-%20Enterprise%20AI%20Onboarding%20&%20Compliance%20Accelerator%20(Agentic%20LMS)/src/api/chat.py)
> - [supervisor.py](file:///d:/ProjectAI/LangGraph%20-%20Enterprise%20AI%20Onboarding%20&%20Compliance%20Accelerator%20(Agentic%20LMS)/src/api/supervisor.py)

### 4.1. Create Session
- **Endpoint:** `POST /api/v1/sessions`
- **Request Body:** `SessionCreateRequest`
  ```json
  {
    "employee_name": "Willy Hanafi",
    "employee_role": "Software Engineer"
  }
  ```
- **Response:** `SessionCreateResponse` (200 OK)
  ```json
  {
    "session_id": "a1b2c3d4-...",
    "welcome_message": "Welcome, Willy! Based on your role...",
    "syllabus": [
      "SOP-HR-01: Code of Conduct",
      "SOP-ENG-01: Secure Coding Guidelines",
      "SOP-SEC-01: InfoSec & Data Protection",
      "SOP-SEC-02: Access Control"
    ]
  }
  ```
- **Error:** `500` if graph invocation fails.

> [!WARNING]
> **PRD v1 Bug (Fixed):** The previous draft used `trainee_name` and `trainee_role` as field names. The actual backend Pydantic model uses `employee_name` and `employee_role`. Using the wrong field names would cause a `422 Unprocessable Entity` error.

### 4.2. Get Session Status
- **Endpoint:** `GET /api/v1/sessions/{session_id}/status`
- **Response:** `SessionStatusResponse` (200 OK)
  ```json
  {
    "session_id": "a1b2c3d4-...",
    "employee_name": "Willy Hanafi",
    "employee_role": "Software Engineer",
    "current_topic": "SOP-ENG-01: Secure Coding Guidelines",
    "completed_topics": ["SOP-HR-01: Code of Conduct"],
    "syllabus": ["SOP-HR-01", "SOP-ENG-01", "SOP-SEC-01", "SOP-SEC-02"],
    "quiz_score": 45,
    "is_certified": false,
    "requires_human_review": false,
    "current_agent": "explainer_node"
  }
  ```
- **Error:** `404` if session not found. `500` if checkpointer fails.

> [!NOTE]
> This endpoint was **missing from PRD v1**. It is critical for the Sidebar's `<SyllabusTracker />` and `<ScorePanel />` components to fetch initial state when the page loads (in case the user refreshes the browser mid-session).

### 4.3. Chat (SSE Streaming)
- **Endpoint:** `POST /api/v1/sessions/{session_id}/chat`
- **Request Body:** `ChatRequest`
  ```json
  { "message": "Tell me about the secure coding guidelines" }
  ```
- **Response:** `Content-Type: text/event-stream`

  The stream emits the following event types in order:

  | Event Name | Data Shape | Frontend Action |
  |---|---|---|
  | `agent_start` | `{"agent": "explainer_node"}` | Show typing indicator, display agent name |
  | `token` | `{"content": "According to..."}` | Append text to current assistant bubble |
  | `agent_end` | `{"agent": "explainer_node"}` | Hide typing indicator |
  | `state_update` | `{"current_topic": "...", "quiz_score": 45, "completed_topics": [...], "is_certified": false}` | Update Sidebar state |
  | `requires_approval` | `{"message": "Awaiting supervisor...", "pending_node": ["certifier_node"]}` | Show `<SupervisorModal />`, disable input |
  | `error` | `{"detail": "Error message"}` | Show error toast |
  | `done` | `{}` | Re-enable input, finalize message |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Edge Case — Non-Streaming JSON Responses:**
> If the session is already certified or already awaiting approval, the backend does NOT return an SSE stream. Instead, it returns a regular JSON `ChatResponse`:
> ```json
> { "session_id": "...", "agent": "system", "message": "Already certified.", "requires_approval": false }
> ```
> The frontend must check the `Content-Type` header of the response:
> - `text/event-stream` → Parse as SSE stream
> - `application/json` → Parse as JSON and display as system message

### 4.4. Chat (Synchronous Fallback)
- **Endpoint:** `POST /api/v1/sessions/{session_id}/chat/sync`
- **Request Body:** `ChatRequest` (same as 4.3)
- **Response:** `ChatResponse` (200 OK)
  ```json
  {
    "session_id": "a1b2c3d4-...",
    "agent": "explainer_node",
    "message": "According to SOP-ENG-01, all code must undergo...",
    "requires_approval": false
  }
  ```

> [!NOTE]
> This endpoint was **missing from PRD v1**. It exists in the backend as a non-streaming alternative, useful for debugging and automated tests. The frontend can use it as a fallback if SSE parsing fails.

### 4.5. Supervisor Approve
- **Endpoint:** `POST /api/v1/sessions/{session_id}/approve`
- **Request Body:** `SupervisorActionRequest` (OPTIONAL body — can be empty)
  ```json
  { "feedback": "Excellent performance. Approved." }
  ```
- **Response:** `SupervisorActionResponse` (200 OK)
  ```json
  {
    "session_id": "a1b2c3d4-...",
    "action": "approved",
    "message": "🎉 Congratulations! You are now certified...",
    "is_certified": true
  }
  ```
- **Errors:** `404` session not found. `400` session not waiting for approval.

> [!WARNING]
> **PRD v1 Bug (Fixed):** The previous draft showed `{ "reason": "..." }` as the request field. The actual Pydantic model uses `feedback` (not `reason`), and it's an `Optional` field — the body can be omitted entirely.

### 4.6. Supervisor Reject
- **Endpoint:** `POST /api/v1/sessions/{session_id}/reject`
- **Request Body:** `SupervisorActionRequest` (OPTIONAL body)
  ```json
  { "feedback": "Needs to review Data Privacy section again." }
  ```
- **Response:** `SupervisorActionResponse` (200 OK)
  ```json
  {
    "session_id": "a1b2c3d4-...",
    "action": "rejected",
    "message": "Certification rejected. Trainee will receive additional tutoring...",
    "is_certified": false
  }
  ```

