## 5. Gap Analysis vs. PRD v1

The following table summarizes all issues found in the original PRD v1 and corrections applied in v2:

| # | Issue in PRD v1 | Severity | Fix in v2 |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | **Wrong field names** in Session Create: used `trainee_name`/`trainee_role` | 🔴 Critical | Changed to `employee_name`/`employee_role` (matches Pydantic schema) |
| 2 | **Wrong field names** in Supervisor: used `reason` | 🔴 Critical | Changed to `feedback` (matches `SupervisorActionRequest` schema) |
| 3 | **Missing `GET /status` endpoint** | 🟡 Major | Added Section 4.2 with full response schema |
| 4 | **Missing `POST /chat/sync` fallback** | 🟡 Major | Added Section 4.4 |
| 5 | **Missing SSE events** `agent_start`, `agent_end` | 🟡 Major | Added to SSE event table in Section 4.3 |
| 6 | **Session Create response** was incomplete (missing `syllabus[]` and `welcome_message`) | 🟡 Major | Fixed to match `SessionCreateResponse` Pydantic model |
| 7 | **SSE `token` format** was wrong: showed bare string, actual is `{"content": "..."}` | 🟡 Major | Fixed to match actual JSON wrapper in `chat.py` line 108 |
| 8 | **SSE `state_update` format** was wrong: showed `{"score": 20, "completed_sops": [...]}` | 🟡 Major | Fixed to `{"current_topic", "quiz_score", "completed_topics", "is_certified"}` per `chat.py` line 119-124 |
| 9 | **Missing edge case** for non-SSE responses from chat endpoint | 🟡 Major | Added Content-Type detection guidance |
| 10 | **No View 4 wireframe** (Post-Certification state) | 🟢 Minor | Added View 4: Certification Complete |
| 11 | **No error handling specification** in UI | 🟢 Minor | Added FR-04 requirement and `error` event handling |
| 12 | **Role input** was free-text (risks typos breaking Planner) | 🟢 Minor | Changed to dropdown select with predefined roles |
| 13 | **CORS** not mentioned — required for localhost cross-origin | 🟢 Minor | CORS already enabled in `server.py` line 106-112. No frontend action needed. |

---

## 6. Non-Functional Requirements

| Category | Requirement | Target |
|---|---|---|
| **Performance** | Time from user message to first visible token | < 2 seconds |
| **Accessibility** | Keyboard navigation for all interactive elements | Tab-navigable |
| **Browser Support** | Chrome, Firefox, Edge (latest 2 versions) | Functional |
| **Bundle Size** | Initial JS bundle (gzipped) | < 200 KB |
| **Design** | Dark mode, glassmorphism, micro-animations | Premium aesthetic |

---

## 7. Technology Decisions

| Decision | Choice | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| **Framework** | React 19 via Vite | Fastest dev server. Pure SPA (no SSR needed). No "Double Backend" conflict with FastAPI. |
| **Styling** | CSS Modules (`.module.css`) | Scoped styles per component. No global class collision. No Tailwind dependency. |
| **Icons** | Lucide React | Lightweight, tree-shakeable, modern icon set. |
| **HTTP Client** | Native `fetch()` API | No axios dependency needed. `ReadableStream` for SSE parsing. |
| **State** | React `useState` + Context | Simple enough for single-page dashboard. No Redux overhead. |
| **Fonts** | Google Fonts: Inter | Clean, professional, widely used in modern SaaS dashboards. |
